        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 8 at 5:46PM CDT until September 8 at 6:45PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southern Beaver County in the Panhandle of Oklahoma...
Northwestern Lipscomb County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Northeastern Ochiltree County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 645 PM CDT.

* At 545 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 6 miles southwest
of Elmwood, or 16 miles northeast of Perryton, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Hail damage to vehicles is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Booker, Darrouzett, Elmwood, and Balko.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
